==English==

===Etymology===
The word is derived from the Swift Boat Veterans for Truth broadcast during the 2004 United States presidential election campaign in which the myth of John Kerry's military heroism was burst.

===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

To correct a politician's false representations of his past, especially with respect to heroism.

====Usage notes====
A politician is swiftboated when the truth of his past is made known.

